<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Martinez</ENAMEX> appointed to finance committee
Newly sworn in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">City Council</ENAMEX> member <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Raul Martinez</ENAMEX> this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">past Monday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">night</TIMEX> was selected to serve as a member of the city's finance committee.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Martinez</ENAMEX> replaces former Councilman Alex de la Cruz on the finance committee, whom <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Martinez</ENAMEX> also replaced on the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">City Council</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Martinez</ENAMEX> will serve on the finance committee with Mayor <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Pro-tem George Greenway</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Councilman Jim Sarducci</ENAMEX>.
Among the duties of the finance committee is to keep track of the city's financial expenditures.
